sql:
SELECT site_id, COUNT(permission_id) AS permission_count
FROM planning_permissions
GROUP BY site_id;

external_knowledge:
- Performance variance is a measure of how much actual performance deviates from the target value; 
- Approved sites are those with a planning status of 'approved', indicating that they have met all necessary conditions and regulations; 
- Cumulative financial value represents the total financial value of each site, calculated by summing up all financial data associated with the site; 
- Environmental risks and opportunities refer to potential negative and positive impacts on the environment, respectively, associated with each site.

sql:
SELECT site_id, COUNT(stakeholder_id) AS stakeholder_count
FROM site_stakeholders
GROUP BY site_id;

SELECT financial_type, AVG(financial_value) AS average_value
FROM site_financial_data
GROUP BY financial_type;
